<worksheet label="ws-PA-changing-quadratic">
  <exploration xml:id="PA-changing-quadratic">
    <introduction>
      <p>
		A water balloon is tossed vertically from a fifth story window.  Its height, <m>h</m>, in meters, at time <m>t</m>, in seconds, is modeled by the function
		<me>
			h = q(t) = -5t^2 + 20t + 25
		</me>.
	</p>
      <p/>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="PA-changing-quadratic-task-0">
      <statement>
        <p>
					Execute appropriate computations to complete both of the following tables.  
				</p>
        <sidebyside widths="48% 48%" margins="0%" valign="bottom">
          <table xml:id="T-PA-changing-quadratic-heights">
            <title>Function values for <m>h</m> at select inputs.</title>
            <tabular>
              <row bottom="minor">
                <cell>
                  <m>t</m>
                </cell>
                <cell>
                  <m>h = q(t)</m>
                </cell>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell>
                  <m>0</m>
                </cell>
                <cell>
                  <m>q(0) = 25</m>
                </cell>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell>
                  <m>1</m>
                </cell>
                <cell/>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell>
                  <m>2</m>
                </cell>
                <cell/>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell>
                  <m>3</m>
                </cell>
                <cell/>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell>
                  <m>4</m>
                </cell>
                <cell/>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell>
                  <m>5</m>
                </cell>
                <cell/>
              </row>
            </tabular>
          </table>
          <table xml:id="T-PA-changing-quadratic-AVs">
            <title>Average rates of change for <m>h</m> on select intervals.</title>
            <tabular>
              <row bottom="minor">
                <cell>
                  <m>[a,b]</m>
                </cell>
                <cell>
                  <m>AV_{[a,b]}</m>
                </cell>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell>
                  <m>[0,1]</m>
                </cell>
                <cell><m>AV_{[0,1]} = 15</m> m/s</cell>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell>
                  <m>[1,2]</m>
                </cell>
                <cell/>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell>
                  <m>[2,3]</m>
                </cell>
                <cell/>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell>
                  <m>[3,4]</m>
                </cell>
                <cell/>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell>
                  <m>[4,5]</m>
                </cell>
                <cell/>
              </row>
              <row>
                <cell colspan="2"/>
              </row>
            </tabular>
          </table>
        </sidebyside>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer/>
      <solution/>
    </task>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="PA-changing-quadratic-task-1">
      <statement>
        <p>
					What pattern(s) do you observe in <xref ref="T-PA-changing-quadratic-heights">Tables</xref> and <xref ref="T-PA-changing-quadratic-AVs"/>?
				</p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer/>
      <solution/>
    </task>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="PA-changing-quadratic-task-2">
      <statement>
        <p>
					Explain why <m>h = q(t)</m> is not a linear function.  Use <xref ref="D-linear-function">Definition</xref> in your response.
				</p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer/>
      <solution/>
    </task>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="PA-changing-quadratic-task-3">
      <statement>
        <p>
					What is the average velocity of the water balloon in the final second before it lands?  How does this value compare to the average velocity on the time interval <m>[4.9, 5]</m>?
				</p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer/>
      <solution/>
    </task>
  </exploration>
</worksheet>
